{"questionId":"22536","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Three points&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>B</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;lie on the plane&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Π</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Plane <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Π</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> has equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The plane <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Π</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math> is given by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>. The line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math> and the plane <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Π</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math> intersect at the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence find the coordinates of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math>&nbsp;has coordinates &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfr